\f1 \cf2 \strokec2 Good question. Let me think through this carefully for REGAL specifically.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 What REGAL actually is
\f1\b0 \
REGAL is the Phase 3 trial of\'a0
\f2\b imetelstat
\f1\b0 \'a0(Geron's telomerase inhibitor) in\'a0
\f2\b lower-risk MDS
\f1\b0 \'a0patients who are transfusion-dependent and relapsed/refractory to ESAs \'97 not AML CR2. So the poster's biological cap argument about AML CR2 being "relentlessly aggressive with no long tail" is being applied to the\'a0
\f2\b wrong disease
\f1\b0 .\
\

\f2\b Does a cure fraction make sense in lower-risk MDS?
\f1\b0 \
This is where it gets genuinely complicated:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Lower-risk MDS is\'a0
\f2\b not uniformly fatal in the short term
\f1\b0 \'a0\'97 patients can live years to decades. Long natural history tails exist even without treatment, making it very hard to distinguish a cure fraction from just... the natural history of an indolent disease.\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Imetelstat's mechanism (telomerase inhibition) could theoretically drive deep clonal suppression, but\'a0
\f2\b transfusion independence (TI) is the endpoint
\f1\b0 , not OS. TI responses in MDS can be durable but also relapse.\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The event velocity deceleration the poster describes could just as plausibly reflect\'a0
\f2\b natural MDS heterogeneity
\f1\b0 \'a0\'97 some patients have very indolent disease regardless of treatment.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 The honest answer
\f1\b0 \
A cure fraction is\'a0
\f2\b less justified here than in almost any other oncology context
\f1\b0 \'a0because:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The control arm would also show a long tail\
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 You can't separate drug effect from disease indolence without the\'a0
\f2\b comparative
\f1\b0 \'a0KM shape\
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The two-anchor fitting approach ignores the control arm entirely\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The poster is essentially modeling the treatment arm in isolation, which makes the cure-fraction inference nearly unfalsifiable from the data they're using.\
What's your read on the actual REGAL efficacy data?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

