\f1 \cf2 \strokec2 Great question. Given you're working from\'a0
\f2\b publicly available summary data
\f1\b0 \'a0(no patient-level data), here's how I'd think about building this rigorously:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 What you actually have to work with
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Two event count anchors (60 at mo 46, 72 at mo 58) \'97 SEC filings\
\ls6\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Possibly published interim KM curves you can\'a0
\f2\b digitize
\f1\b0 \'a0(using WebPlotDigitizer)\
\ls6\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Historical AML CR2 natural history data for control arm benchmarking\
\ls6\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Any published response rate / TI duration data from earlier GPS trials\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 The modeling stack I'd build
\f1\b0 \

\f2\b Step 1 \'97 Digitize the KM curve
\f1\b0 \'a0if one exists from any publication or conference presentation. This gives you way more than two anchors.\

\f2\b Step 2 \'97 Fit competing survival models
\f1\b0 \'a0to the digitized data:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Standard (Weibull, Log-Normal, Gamma)\
\ls7\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Cure-fraction mixture model\
\ls7\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Compare via AIC/BIC \'97 not just "does it fit the anchors"\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 Step 3 \'97 Benchmark against the control arm
\f1\b0 \'a0or historical AML CR2 OS. The cure fraction argument only holds if the treatment arm tail is\'a0
\f3\i meaningfully above
\f1\i0 \'a0what you'd expect from natural history.\

\f2\b Step 4 \'97 Sensitivity analysis
\f1\b0 \'a0on your key assumptions (cure fraction %, BAT mOS)\
\

\f2\b The critical question before building anything
\f1\b0 \
Do you have access to an actual KM curve from GPS publications or conference abstracts? That determines whether this is worth doing rigorously or is fundamentally limited by the two-anchor problem.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

