\f1 \cf2 \strokec2 This is actually a really constrained and answerable question given what we know about GPS's mechanism and the AML CR2 population.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 Working from the biology up
\f1\b0 \
GPS works by generating WT1-specific cytotoxic T-cells. For a patient to fall into the "cured" fraction they need to:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Be in CR2 at enrollment (already selected)\
\ls8\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Generate a meaningful immune response to the vaccine\
\ls8\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Have that response be durable enough to maintain remission surveillance\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Each of those is a filter.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 The immunological response rate data
\f1\b0 \
From earlier GPS trials, WT1-specific immune responses were observed in roughly\'a0
\f2\b 40-60%
\f1\b0 \'a0of vaccinated patients. But immune response \uc0\u8800  clinical cure. The conversion rate from immune responder to durable remission is substantially lower.\
\

\f2\b My honest estimate for the cure fraction parameter
\f1\b0 \
Probably\'a0
\f2\b 10-25%
\f1\b0 \'a0is the defensible range to test, with:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls9\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 ~15%
\f1\b0 \'a0as the central estimate\
\ls9\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 10%
\f1\b0 \'a0as the conservative bound\
\ls9\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 25%
\f1\b0 \'a0as the optimistic bound\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 This is consistent with what cure-fraction models in other cancer vaccine settings have produced, and aligns with the subset of AML CR2 patients who historically achieve long-term remission on any therapy.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 The important caveat
\f1\b0 \
The cure fraction parameter is extremely sensitive to\'a0
\f2\b follow-up length
\f1\b0 \'a0in the model. With only 72 total events and relatively short follow-up, the model can't reliably distinguish a 15% cure fraction from a 20% one. Your sensitivity analysis across that range matters more than picking a point estimate.\
Do you want to actually build this in Python?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

