\f1 \cf2 \strokec2 Great question \'97 this is an important mechanistic distinction.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 HLA-A*02:01\'a0is MHC Class I 
\f6 \uc0\u8594 
\f2  CD8+ (cytotoxic T-cells)
\f1\b0 \
That's the primary GPS epitope. MHC Class I presents intracellular peptides to CD8+ T-cells, which then directly kill WT1-expressing leukemic blasts. This is the main effector mechanism you want for tumor killing.\
\

\f2\b The CD4+ side (MHC Class II)
\f1\b0 \
GPS also contains epitopes designed to activate CD4+ helper T-cells via MHC Class II presentation. The relevant alleles there are\'a0
\f2\b HLA-DR
\f1\b0 \'a0alleles, particularly\'a0
\f2\b HLA-DRB1
\f1\b0 \'a0variants. CD4+ T-cells don't kill directly but are critical for:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls15\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Sustaining CD8+ T-cell responses long-term\
\ls15\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Supporting immune memory\
\ls15\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 B-cell activation\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 This is actually why GPS was designed as a multi-epitope vaccine \'97 the CD4+ helper response is what potentially makes the CD8+ killing\'a0
\f2\b durable
\f1\b0 \'a0rather than just transient.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 Why this complicates your model
\f1\b0 \
A patient needs\'a0
\f2\b both arms
\f1\b0 \'a0working well for a durable cure-fraction response:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls16\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 HLA-A*02:01+ 
\f5 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  strong CD8+ killing\
\ls16\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Favorable HLA-DR 
\f5 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  strong CD4+ support\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Patients who are HLA-A*02:01+ but have poor HLA-DR compatibility for the GPS CD4+ epitopes may mount a strong initial response that fades. That's the difference between a responder and a\'a0
\f2\b cured
\f1\b0 \'a0patient in the mixture model.\
\
Do you want to look up which specific HLA-DR alleles the GPS CD4+ epitopes were designed around? That would let you build a more refined two-dimensional HLA stratification.\
