    \cf17 \strokec17 return\cf15 \strokec15  median_os / \cf18 \strokec18 (\cf15 \strokec15 np\cf18 \strokec18 .\cf15 \strokec15 log\cf18 \strokec18 (\cf20 \strokec20 2\cf18 \strokec18 )\cf15 \strokec15  ** \cf18 \strokec18 (\cf20 \strokec20 1\cf15 \strokec15  / shape\cf18 \strokec18 ))\cf15 \strokec15 \
\
\cf17 \strokec17 def\cf15 \strokec15  \cf21 \strokec21 weibull_survival\cf18 \strokec18 (\cf15 \strokec15 t\cf18 \strokec18 ,\cf15 \strokec15  median_os\cf18 \strokec18 ,\cf15 \strokec15  shape\cf18 \strokec18 ):\cf15 \strokec15 \
    lam = weibull_lambda\cf18 \strokec18 (\cf15 \strokec15 median_os\cf18 \strokec18 ,\cf15 \strokec15  shape\cf18 \strokec18 )\cf15 \strokec15 \
    \cf17 \strokec17 return\cf15 \strokec15  np\cf18 \strokec18 .\cf15 \strokec15 exp\cf18 \strokec18 (\cf15 \strokec15 -\cf18 \strokec18 ((\cf15 \strokec15 t / lam\cf18 \strokec18 )\cf15 \strokec15  ** shape\cf18 \strokec18 ))\cf15 \cb1 \strokec15 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 The Weibull survival function is S(t) = exp(-(t/\uc0\u955 )^k). The problem is you don't directly observe \u955  \'97 you observe the median OS from the literature. So\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf7 \cb8 \strokec7 weibull_lambda
