\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 These are approximations, not exact statistics \'97 worth being explicit about that.\
The HR formula uses the ratio of log-survivals (= ratio of cumulative hazards) at the BAT median OS timepoint. This is a point estimate rather than a proper weighted log-rank HR, which would require integrating over all timepoints weighted by the number at risk.\
The p-value uses a normal approximation to the log-rank statistic: z \uc0\u8776  -log(HR) \'d7 \u8730 (D/4) where D is the number of events. This is a rough approximation \'97 the real p-value requires the actual event times. Treat both numbers as directional, not precise.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

