\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 A nested loop over two axes \'97 BAT median OS and cure fraction \'97 computing HR and p-value at every combination. The output is two 9\'d79 grids that become the heatmaps in panels 5 and 6. This is the most important part of the model analytically because it shows you how robust the conclusions are to your most uncertain assumptions. The contour lines on the heatmap tell you exactly where you'd cross HR=0.75 or p=0.05 if the real world is more pessimistic than your base case.\
