\f1 \cf2 \strokec2 Honest answer \'97 I didn't calculate them from data. They were\'a0
\f2\b assumptions I set as defaults
\f1\b0 , not derived values. Let me be transparent about where each came from.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 BAT median OS (default: 11 months)
\f1\b0 \
This came from the historical AML CR2 literature, not from REGAL's actual control arm data. The general range cited in AML CR2 studies for patients not eligible for transplant is roughly\'a0
\f2\b 8-16 months
\f1\b0 . I picked 11 months as a mid-range default. The actual sources would be papers like:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls42\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Ghez et al., historical AML CR2 cohorts\
\ls42\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 NCCAP AML guidelines citing BAT outcomes\
\ls42\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Prior salvage chemotherapy trials in this population\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 This is why the sensitivity heatmap sweeps BAT mOS from 8 to 16 \'97 because\'a0
\f2\b that range is the real uncertainty
\f1\b0 , and the HR and p-value are highly sensitive to where the true BAT control arm lands.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 GPS median OS for non-cured patients (default: 20 months)
\f1\b0 \
This one is even more assumption-driven. There's no direct data for the median OS of the\'a0
\f3\i non-cured susceptible
\f1\i0 \'a0subpopulation from GPS trials because:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls43\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Phase 2 was underpowered and didn't report it that way\
\ls43\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 You'd need to fit the mixture model to patient-level data to properly estimate it\
\ls43\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 It's a latent parameter \'97 you never directly observe who is in the susceptible group\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 I set 20 months based on rough reasoning that GPS non-cured patients probably do somewhat better than BAT (11 months) due to the vaccine's partial immune effect, but not dramatically so. It's essentially a\'a0
\f2\b tuning parameter
\f1\b0 .\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

