\f2\b \cf2 The key insight
\f1\b0 \
The GPS arm in REGAL is a\'a0
\f2\b mixture
\f1\b0 \'a0of responders and non-responders. So the GPS median OS for the\'a0
\f3\i non-cured susceptible
\f1\i0 \'a0subpopulation is essentially a weighted combination of:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls45\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The non-responder survival (they get no benefit)\
\ls45\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The responding-but-not-cured patients (they get partial benefit but eventually relapse)\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 Bounding the range
\f1\b0 \

\f2\b Lower bound \'97 non-responders only:
\f1\b0 \
Non-responders had median OS of\'a0
\f2\b 35.8 months
\f1\b0 \'a0from time of diagnosis. If you adjust to time from CR2 enrollment it's somewhat shorter, probably\'a0
\f2\b ~20-25 months
\f1\b0 . This is your floor \'97 if GPS has zero effect on non-responders, the susceptible subpopulation looks like this.\

\f2\b Upper bound \'97 partial responders:
\f1\b0 \
Responders who aren't cured (i.e. they're in the 42.5% of responders who eventually relapsed) had their curve still declining at 65 months with maybe 10-15% remaining. That implies a median somewhere around\'a0
\f2\b 40-50 months
\f1\b0 \'a0for that subset \'97 but this is very uncertain given the small n.\

