\f2\b \cf2 For the CD4+ arm (MHC Class II)
\f1\b0 \
The two long peptides (331-L and 427-L) are specifically designed to be processed and presented by\'a0
\f2\b HLA-DR molecules
\f1\b0 . Three WT1 peptides (328\'96349, 423\'96441 and 122\'96140) bind to multiple HLA-DRB1 molecules common in Caucasian populations. Adding flank residues allows these peptides to bind to a broader range of HLA class II molecules, and therefore could stimulate T cells from a large percentage of the targeted population.\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/medicine-and-dentistry/galinpepimut-s"}}{\fldrslt 
