\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 It's consistent with a\'a0
\f2\b very high
\f1\b0 \'a0P(cure | CD4 responder)\
\ls58\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 It suggests CD4+ response is not just a bystander effect \'97 it appears to be mechanistically linked to durable remission\
\ls58\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 It aligns with the biological story \'97 CD4+ help maintains CD8+ memory long term, so CD4+ responders who also had CD8+ activity would have the most durable responses\
