\f2\b\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 Why this matters for interpretation
\f1\b0 \
The HR and p-value in the model are comparing those two fundamentally different survival shapes \'97 not just shifting one curve relative to another. A standard proportional hazards assumption (which underlies the log-rank test) is actually\'a0
\f2\b violated
\f1\b0 \'a0when one arm has a cure fraction and the other doesn't, because the hazard ratio isn't constant over time. Early on the curves look similar, but late the GPS arm stops declining while BAT keeps going. The HR changes over time.\
This is actually a known issue for cure fraction trials \'97 the log-rank test is underpowered relative to tests that specifically account for the non-proportional hazards. It's worth keeping in mind when interpreting the p-value approximation in the model.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

